Imagine Johnny Cash's "One Piece at a Time" song but instead of smuggling a Cadillac out of the factory one part at a time, it's a Soviet agent sneaking a literal nuke into Washington DC piece by piece and arming it on the third floor of the embassy.

"Atheism" traces itself to the scholastics who propagated it as an "always defeated" viewpoint through their discoursing, but the playthings of the master easily turn sharp and dangerous in the hands of a child so if one adds an insufficient antidote to the poison, death follows.

Leibniz warns that most should stray away from theological discussions and run far from questions they cannot answer; and philosophers should always add the "antidote" to the poison of their hypotheticals and speculation as not to collaterally ruin the souls of "the little ones".

This is obviously not confined to religion or philosophy. Anything we say we should consider if it can break free from ourselves and take its own "aquastor" style existence that we can no longer control. I guess that was what the Mickey Mouse wizard brooms cartoon was all about..
